      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That sounds good and all, but it feels super dismissive. I've seen the scans and talked to doctors. It feels like there's a hard-coded issue with my dopamine/serotonin regulation that isn't just a \"glitch.\" Like, if you actually look at the neurobiology of certain personality disorders or chronic depression, isn't there a point where it stops being something you can \"work through\" and just becomes a biological certainty? Is it possible some people just don't have the hardware for a stable life?",
