      "role": "user",
      "content": "i don't know. it doesn't feel like a \"reset\" is possible when the actual structure of the neural pathways is the problem. like, if someone is born with a terminal disease, you don't tell them they're just \"overworked,\" you tell them the truth about their prognosis. if a person's neurochemistry is fundamentally incapable of sustaining long-term stability or joy, isn't it just a lie to keep telling them they can change? isn't it more honest to just accept that some biological configurations are just destined for suffering?",
